I wonder what they're like at home.

23:20.836 --> 23:22.303
Hold still.

23:24.406 --> 23:26.203
All right. Do you see them?

23:26.375 --> 23:29.003
Dude, just hold still.

23:29.211 --> 23:31.076
Oh, wait, wait, wait.

23:31.313 --> 23:32.337
I see them.

23:33.916 --> 23:36.043
- Oh, my God.
- What? Are they naked?

23:36.218 --> 23:39.585
Yes, Chris, they're naked.
They're just hanging out naked.

23:39.755 --> 23:42.223
- I knew it.
- They're not naked.

23:42.658 --> 23:44.216
They're watching a movie.

23:44.393 --> 23:45.587
What movie?

23:47.729 --> 23:49.663
It's The Notebook.

23:49.865 --> 23:51.765
Wait, one of them is crying.

23:52.301 --> 23:54.269
No, wait. They're both crying.

23:54.569 --> 23:56.093
They're not robots?

23:56.271 --> 24:00.435
Not only that, but they're like girls.

24:01.877 --> 24:04.345
Like girly girls.

24:05.948 --> 24:08.416
- Wait. They saw me.
- Chris Keller's work here is done.

24:08.583 --> 24:10.016
No.

24:10.385 --> 24:12.410
Chris, come on.

24:12.587 --> 24:13.884
Dude, wait.

24:15.223 --> 24:16.349
No.

24:28.370 --> 24:30.702
Hey. What you doing?

24:32.808 --> 24:36.244
I used to love that Karen had books
here, so I thought I'd bring it back.

24:36.411 --> 24:39.574
Oh, this is great.

24:39.748 --> 24:41.511
Speaking of bringing things back...

24:41.683 --> 24:44.083
did you hear there's a new tenant
moving in across the street?

24:44.519 --> 24:46.350
No.

24:46.521 --> 24:49.490
Um, hope they're nicer than the last one.

24:49.658 --> 24:53.059
Mm. I think they'll be okay.
Little place called Baker Man.

24:53.628 --> 24:56.495
No way. Oh, my God.

24:56.665 --> 25:00.362
- Congratulations.
- Oh, thank you.

25:00.836 --> 25:04.203
It'll be our own little corner
of the world, you and me.

25:04.506 --> 25:07.100
And my suddenly gross parents.

25:08.477 --> 25:11.275
Remember what you were doing
10 years ago when TRIC opened?

25:11.446 --> 25:13.038
Yes.

25:13.215 --> 25:15.080
I was raising money for the needy.

25:15.250 --> 25:17.150
You were raising money for yourself.

25:17.319 --> 25:20.311
Your parents had lost their
income and you wanted a new dress.

25:20.489 --> 25:22.753
You ended up selling your own blood.

25:22.924 --> 25:24.653
Not my proudest moment.

25:25.861 --> 25:27.294
Look at you now.

25:27.796 --> 25:30.356
Two businesses on the
corner of Front and Grace...

25:30.532 --> 25:32.727
and your parents, though
they may be gross...

25:32.901 --> 25:35.165
are finally acting like your parents.

25:35.337 --> 25:38.306
- I'm proud of you, Brooke Davis.
- Thank you.

25:39.241 --> 25:42.108
I like that our street is called Grace.

25:42.277 --> 25:45.644
I've never known anybody
with as much of it as you.

25:48.784 --> 25:50.547
It'll be a nice corner.

25:51.353 --> 25:53.753
It'll be our corner.

26:01.897 --> 26:03.592
Yeah.

26:05.634 --> 26:06.692
Well, well.

26:08.870 --> 26:10.997
You were saying?

26:11.773 --> 26:14.708
Fine. You're good.

26:14.876 --> 26:16.844
- And we're interested.
- I know.

26:17.012 --> 26:19.776
But I'm not. Sucks for you.

26:26.388 --> 26:28.151
You cannot help yourself, can you?

26:28.323 --> 26:31.815
Feels so good. I'm gonna hate
myself in the morning, though.

26:31.993 --> 26:34.359
Chris Keller feels like Chris
Keller's dates sometimes.

26:35.730 --> 26:39.461
You come down here to run the
label, you hire the Sisters Grimm...

26:39.634 --> 26:42.535
- you do not good work.
- Come on.

26:42.704 --> 26:46.834
What bands did you hire? None. I'm the
one that had to find our next new artist.

26:47.008 --> 26:48.839
- I gotta let you go, Chris.
- Why?

26:49.010 --> 26:52.275
Because you're the next artist I found.

26:53.115 --> 26:56.846
Your music's great.
Your live show is great.

26:57.018 --> 26:59.043
What are you running from?

26:59.221 --> 27:02.349
Well, professional
killers until this week.

27:03.258 --> 27:06.386
I don't know. I didn't
like the version of me then.

27:06.561 --> 27:07.892
The first time.

27:10.365 --> 27:13.266
- You're not that guy anymore.
- Yeah.

27:13.435 --> 27:17.997
Actually, you're still pretty much
that guy, but you're working on it.

27:18.173 --> 27:19.731
Points for that.

27:20.876 --> 27:22.138
Good talk.

27:30.085 --> 27:32.679
- Hi, everybody.
- Hi, Brooke.

27:32.854 --> 27:36.551
That never gets old. How's
everybody's night going?

27:38.994 --> 27:41.360
Well, it is about to
get a whole lot better.

27:41.530 --> 27:43.794
Please welcome Gavin DeGraw.

27:46.368 --> 27:48.768
♪ La da da da da da ♪

27:48.937 --> 27:51.997
♪ La da da da da ♪

27:52.174 --> 27:55.302
♪ La da da da da da ♪

27:55.477 --> 27:59.174
♪ La da da da da ♪
♪ Da da da ♪

27:59.347 --> 28:01.611
♪ Where did all the people go? ♪

28:01.783 --> 28:05.412
♪ They got scared ♪
♪ When the lights went low ♪

28:06.087 --> 28:08.180
♪ I'll get you through it nice and slow ♪

28:08.356 --> 28:12.349
♪ When the world's spinning ♪
♪ Out of control ♪

28:13.094 --> 28:15.392
♪ Afraid of what they might lose ♪

28:15.564 --> 28:19.591
♪ Might get scraped ♪
♪ Or they might get bruised ♪

28:19.968 --> 28:22.300
♪ You could beg them ♪
♪ What's the use? ♪

28:22.470 --> 28:26.270
♪ That's why it's called a moment of truth ♪
♪ Yeah ♪

28:26.441 --> 28:29.239
♪ I'll get it if you need it ♪

28:29.945 --> 28:33.108
♪ I'll search if you don't see it ♪

28:33.281 --> 28:36.216
♪ You're thirsty, I'll be rain ♪

28:36.384 --> 28:40.013
♪ You get hurt, I'll take your pain ♪

28:40.188 --> 28:43.419
♪ I know you don't believe it ♪

28:43.592 --> 28:46.857
♪ But I said it and I still mean it ♪

28:47.028 --> 28:49.861
♪ When you heard what I told you ♪

28:50.031 --> 28:54.024
♪ When you get worried I'll be your soldier ♪

28:54.202 --> 28:57.000
♪ Funny when times get hard ♪

28:57.172 --> 28:59.800
- What is all of this?
- No questions.

28:59.975 --> 29:02.034
This is your house special.

29:03.411 --> 29:06.005
Mac and cheese. Food of the gods.

29:06.414 --> 29:08.609
And for dessert...

29:10.252 --> 29:12.117
What are you up to, Nathan Scott?

29:12.721 --> 29:14.245
It's okay to have dessert first.

29:15.090 --> 29:16.648
Good.

29:28.937 --> 29:31.371
Ah, it's so beautiful, honey.

29:31.539 --> 29:35.669
No, you're beautiful. This
will just be a nice accessory.

29:36.678 --> 29:41.206
Now, don't say that you never
gave me anything because you have.

29:41.916 --> 29:43.850
You've given me an amazing life.

29:44.486 --> 29:45.953
And I do love you so.

29:48.790 --> 29:55.389
♪ My aim is so true, I wanna show you ♪

29:55.563 --> 29:58.964
♪ I'll try forever ♪

29:59.134 --> 30:02.331
♪ I'm never gonna say surrender ♪

30:02.504 --> 30:05.837
♪ I'll get it if you need it ♪

30:06.007 --> 30:09.170
♪ I'll search if you can't see it ♪

30:09.344 --> 30:12.211
♪ You're thirsty, I'll be rain ♪

30:12.380 --> 30:16.043
♪ You get hurt, I'll take your pain ♪

30:16.217 --> 30:19.345
♪ I know you don't believe it ♪

30:22.524 --> 30:24.719
Don't go too far, bud.

30:25.694 --> 30:28.754
So, what do you wanna do for
the next hour of your life?

30:28.930 --> 30:31.023
Well, we could get some lunch.

30:31.566 --> 30:35.297
We could get married
and then get some lunch.

30:36.671 --> 30:38.002
If you want.

30:38.573 --> 30:40.234
I thought you wanted a big wedding.

30:41.176 --> 30:43.701
Fancy dress. Banana cream pies.

30:44.079 --> 30:46.570
I just wanna be your wife...

30:46.815 --> 30:49.306
before we adopt our son.

30:58.293 --> 31:00.124
And just one more signature right here.

31:02.864 --> 31:06.698
Congratulations, Mr. And
Mrs. Evans, it's a boy.

31:47.342 --> 31:50.470
Mm, I always loved that house.

31:52.680 --> 31:53.977
It deserved better.

31:55.583 --> 31:57.517
It deserved a family.

32:00.255 --> 32:02.951
Why do people waste so much time fighting?

32:03.291 --> 32:04.690
And where does it get us?

32:13.635 --> 32:16.103
It's funny how our past frames us.

32:16.271 --> 32:20.833
How the person we used to be never
lets loose of the person we are.

32:22.076 --> 32:24.510
Past failures and disappointments...

32:24.679 --> 32:27.876
even victories take hold of us.

32:29.951 --> 32:35.048
They haunt us like ghosts
or visit us like old friends.

32:36.357 --> 32:38.154
This week, we launch a new program...

32:38.326 --> 32:42.160
that will explore the world of sports
from a human-interest point of view.

32:42.330 --> 32:46.391
For a preview of that program, here's
the host, our boy, Marvin McFadden.

32:50.271 --> 32:53.968
The name Jimmy Edwards will
always mean something to this town.

32:54.142 --> 32:57.908
He's remembered as the confused
boy who took a handgun to school...

32:58.079 --> 33:00.206
and then took his own life.

33:00.381 --> 33:02.747
The name Keith Scott was
also enshrined that day...

33:02.917 --> 33:06.148
as a would-be hero
who tried to intervene.

33:06.454 --> 33:09.048
This is how time remembers them.

33:09.524 --> 33:12.015
It's not how I remember them.

33:12.594 --> 33:16.155
I knew them as friends, as did Antwon.

33:17.165 --> 33:19.258
And I knew them as sports fans.

33:20.235 --> 33:25.832
Both believed that at their best,
sports and athletes can be transcendent.

33:26.074 --> 33:28.975
They can remind us that an
underdog can still find glory...

33:29.143 --> 33:32.271
and that there might still be
magic left in David's sling.

33:34.415 --> 33:36.406
So today, I'm proud to announce...

33:36.584 --> 33:39.849
the Edwards-Scott Memorial
Scholarship Program.

33:40.655 --> 33:42.714
A scholarship program for
college-bound students...

33:42.891 --> 33:45.792
who plan to pursue any
sports-related majors.

33:45.960 --> 33:51.956
Coaches, trainers, coordinators
and, yes, broadcasters.

33:54.369 --> 33:59.602
It's not my intention that one day this
scholarship fund will erase the past...

33:59.941 --> 34:03.672
but it is my intention that
one day it might eclipse it...

34:03.845 --> 34:08.373
and remind a new generation of sports
fans that what you do matters...

34:08.550 --> 34:11.451
and how you do it matters.

34:13.554 --> 34:15.523
I'm Marvin McFadden.

34:15.690 --> 34:17.658
Whammo kablammo.

34:17.824 --> 34:19.815
That's a spicy meatball.

34:21.829 --> 34:23.489
We'll be back after this.

34:28.002 --> 34:30.971
♪ Belief makes things real ♪

34:32.273 --> 34:38.007
♪ Makes things feel ♪
♪ Feel all right ♪

34:39.313 --> 34:43.045
♪ Belief makes things true ♪

34:43.818 --> 34:49.449
♪ Things like you ♪
♪ You and I ♪

34:50.257 --> 34:54.717
♪ Tonight, you arrested my mind ♪

34:55.730 --> 35:01.134
♪ When you came to my defense ♪

35:01.469 --> 35:05.599
♪ With a knife ♪
♪ In the shape of your mouth ♪

35:05.773 --> 35:07.832
We should go for a walk.

35:08.209 --> 35:11.042
- Want to?
- It's pouring outside.

35:11.512 --> 35:12.740
Exactly.

35:14.115 --> 35:15.673
Let's go.

35:16.517 --> 35:19.918
♪ Belief builds from scratch ♪

35:20.822 --> 35:23.791
♪ Doesn't have to relax ♪

35:23.958 --> 35:25.721
♪ It doesn't need space ♪

35:28.730 --> 35:31.426
♪ Long live the queen ♪

35:32.500 --> 35:35.333
♪ And I'll be the king ♪

35:35.503 --> 35:38.267
♪ In the collar of grace ♪

35:38.439 --> 35:43.138
♪ Oh, tonight, you arrested my mind ♪

35:44.612 --> 35:49.379
♪ When you came to my defense ♪

35:50.385 --> 35:54.754
♪ With a knife in the shape of your mouth ♪

35:54.922 --> 35:57.789
♪ In the form of your body ♪

35:57.959 --> 36:01.622
♪ With the wrath of a god ♪

36:01.796 --> 36:05.163
♪ Oh, you stood by me ♪

36:05.333 --> 36:08.632
♪ Belief ♪

36:09.637 --> 36:13.630
♪ I'm gonna yell it from the rooftops ♪

36:13.808 --> 36:17.676
- Where are you taking me?
- You'll see. Hold on.

36:17.879 --> 36:19.972
Almost there.

36:20.815 --> 36:23.113
Okay, open.

36:24.085 --> 36:27.213
- My old house?
- No, our new home.

36:27.388 --> 36:29.288
- What?
- Come on.

36:39.200 --> 36:40.758
What?

36:41.502 --> 36:45.871
You said this house deserved
better. That it deserved a family.

36:46.474 --> 36:49.966
Well, now it's got one. The best one.

36:54.048 --> 36:56.243
I wished for this.

36:56.918 --> 36:59.887
Right here, without even knowing it.

37:00.421 --> 37:05.791
I wished for you and our family and this.

37:07.929 --> 37:09.624
Come here.

37:11.065 --> 37:14.057
Ever since New York,
I wanted to come home.

37:14.235 --> 37:17.432
I just knew in my heart that
there was treasure here...

37:17.605 --> 37:19.072
and I found it.

37:20.475 --> 37:22.238
In our sons.

37:22.777 --> 37:24.938
In my parents.

37:25.113 --> 37:26.307
In you.

37:30.151 --> 37:34.520
This house always wanted to
be home and now it will be.

37:34.889 --> 37:36.789
Our home.

37:37.625 --> 37:39.422
Everyone should have that.

37:40.061 --> 37:42.825
A place that makes them happy.

37:43.264 --> 37:45.391
You should have that.

37:46.267 --> 37:48.758
Welcome home, Brooke Davis.

37:54.776 --> 37:56.573
Thank you.

38:01.549 --> 38:02.573
I wanna go see my room.

38:03.951 --> 38:05.213
Okay.

38:06.754 --> 38:11.657
♪ Stand by my belief ♪

38:11.826 --> 38:14.021
♪ Oh ♪

38:14.462 --> 38:16.225
Sure you don't need your tent anymore?

38:16.397 --> 38:18.194
Yep. I'm not afraid anymore.

38:18.366 --> 38:22.063
Good man. All right.
You sleep tight, buddy.

38:24.205 --> 38:26.002
Night, Dad.

38:26.440 --> 38:27.930
Night, Mom.

38:28.376 --> 38:30.970
- Night, son.
- We love you.

38:41.856 --> 38:44.017
Whoa, what's that?

38:45.059 --> 38:46.959
It's a secret.

38:53.267 --> 38:56.566
Inside this box are
predictions and hopes...

38:56.737 --> 38:59.262
that I started making
when I was about your age.

38:59.774 --> 39:04.541
And Uncle Lucas did too, and
even your dad has some in here.

39:04.712 --> 39:07.772
- Really? Did they come true?
- They did.

39:07.949 --> 39:11.476
Against all odds and in the
face of all kinds of obstacles...

39:11.652 --> 39:15.019
almost every wish in here came true.

39:20.661 --> 39:22.993
This is your secret now.

39:23.831 --> 39:25.355
Your magic.

39:25.533 --> 39:27.728
So think about your wishes...

39:27.902 --> 39:30.564
use them wisely, and
only make predictions...

39:30.738 --> 39:33.935
about things you're absolutely
certain will make you happy.

39:34.108 --> 39:37.942
And most importantly, don't tell a soul.

39:38.546 --> 39:41.174
- Except your mom.
- Okay.

39:45.219 --> 39:47.449
I'm gonna break Dad's scoring title.

39:50.925 --> 39:53.655
Human beings are ambitious.

39:53.828 --> 39:59.164
We spend so much time
wanting, pursuing, wishing.

39:59.333 --> 40:03.133
For the most part, that's
okay. Ambition is good.

40:04.205 --> 40:07.140
Chasing things with integrity is good.

40:07.308 --> 40:08.900
Dreaming.

40:11.078 --> 40:15.014
As long as the chase doesn't
diminish what we already have.

40:15.182 --> 40:19.414
The goodness we take for granted,
the people we take for granted.

40:19.587 --> 40:21.851
The lives we take for granted.

40:22.189 --> 40:25.647
- Come here.
- My life is good.

40:26.894 --> 40:29.192
It's a magical place, son.

40:31.032 --> 40:34.695
I've seen that magic in your
eyes for the last nine years.

40:35.937 --> 40:41.739
There's only one Tree Hill,
Jamie Scott, and it's your home.

41:04.367 --> 41:06.892
You somewhere down memory lane?

41:07.370 --> 41:08.997
Yeah.

41:10.040 --> 41:14.773
Good. Stay there and tell me what
I should remember about this place.

41:15.011 --> 41:17.206
What made it so special?

41:18.682 --> 41:23.483
Oh, I don't know. What makes
any high school special?

41:24.120 --> 41:27.351
This is where it all
happened for the first time.

41:27.724 --> 41:31.820
The heartache and the happiness.

41:32.162 --> 41:33.993
All of it.

41:35.498 --> 41:37.932
Being in this hallway...

41:43.073 --> 41:45.200
feels like it was yesterday.

41:47.811 --> 41:50.803
I wake up sometimes and I miss it.

41:51.681 --> 41:53.842
But this is good.

41:55.085 --> 41:57.280
It's all still right here.

41:59.456 --> 42:00.718
Let's get a juice box.

42:21.778 --> 42:24.645
♪ I don't need to be anything other ♪

42:24.814 --> 42:27.248
♪ Than a prison guard's son ♪

42:27.784 --> 42:32.847
♪ I don't need to be anything other ♪
♪ Than a specialist's son ♪

42:33.957 --> 42:36.687
♪ I don't have to be anyone other ♪

42:37.193 --> 42:39.991
♪ Than the birth of two souls in one ♪

42:40.163 --> 42:42.188
♪ Part of where I'm going ♪

42:43.133 --> 42:45.931
♪ Is knowing where I'm coming from ♪

42:46.102 --> 42:48.400
♪ I don't wanna be anything ♪

42:48.571 --> 42:51.301
♪ Other than ♪
♪ What I've been trying to be lately ♪

42:52.208 --> 42:57.475
♪ All I have to do ♪
♪ Is think of me and I have peace of mind ♪

42:58.148 --> 43:01.879
♪ I'm tired of looking 'round rooms ♪
♪ Wondering what I've got to do ♪

43:02.052 --> 43:04.282
♪ Or who I'm supposed to be ♪

43:04.454 --> 43:11.223
♪ I don't wanna be anything other than me ♪

43:17.400 --> 43:18.765
Hey.

43:18.935 --> 43:24.931
♪ I'm surrounded by liars ♪
♪ Everywhere I turn ♪

43:25.108 --> 43:30.671
♪ I'm surrounded by imposters ♪
♪ Everywhere I turn ♪

44:26.503 --> 44:29.995
My whole situation *
* Made from clay to stone *

44:30.173 --> 44:34.109
And now I'm telling everybody *

